<h3>Why WordPress Content Teams Should Care</h3>
<p>Publishing velocity determines ranking velocity. Sites that publish 30+ articles per month build <a href="/blog/build-topical-authority/">topical authority</a> faster than sites publishing 2 to 4.</p>
<p>AI agents make high-volume publishing possible without a large team. A single operator can instruct an agent to produce, format, and schedule an entire content calendar. The bottleneck shifts from production to strategy.</p>
<h2>How AI Agents Work With WordPress &#123;#chapter-2&#125;</h2>
<p>AI agents connect to WordPress through the Model Context Protocol, or MCP. This is the technical bridge that lets an agent read and write to your site.</p>
<h3>What Is MCP?</h3>
<p>MCP stands for Model Context Protocol. Anthropic introduced it as a standard way for AI models to interact with external services. WordPress adopted it in October 2025.</p>
<p>Think of MCP as a universal adapter. It gives AI agents like Claude, ChatGPT, and Cursor a structured way to access your site content, analytics, and settings. Before MCP, every integration required custom code.</p>
