<h3>1. Drafting and Publishing Blog Posts</h3>
<p>The primary use case. You instruct the agent with a topic, target keyword, and word count. The agent researches, outlines, writes, and formats the post with proper H2 and H3 structure.</p>
<p>The best agents pull data from your existing content to maintain voice consistency. They also check your category and tag taxonomy before assigning labels. This keeps your <a href="/blog/seo-for-wordpress/">WordPress SEO</a> structure clean.</p>
<h3>2. Building and Updating Landing Pages</h3>
<p>AI agents create full pages with your site design specifications. Need a new service page? Describe the offer, and the agent builds it using your theme block patterns.</p>
<p>This is valuable for businesses running seasonal campaigns or A/B tests. You can spin up landing pages in minutes instead of hours.</p>
<h3>3. Managing Comments</h3>
<p>Comment moderation is tedious. AI agents approve, reply to, or clean up comments based on rules you define. Spam detection improves because the agent learns your site context.</p>
<h3>4. Organizing Categories and Tags</h3>
<p>Taxonomy drift is a real problem on WordPress sites with hundreds of posts. AI agents audit your categories and tags, merge duplicates, and restructure the taxonomy for better <a href="/blog/ai-content-strategy/">AI content strategy</a> alignment.</p>
