<h2>AI Agents vs Traditional WordPress Plugins &#123;#chapter-6&#125;</h2>
<p>WordPress users have relied on plugins for AI content help since 2023. AI agents represent a fundamentally different approach. Understanding the distinction matters for choosing the right setup.</p>
<h3>Plugins: Reactive Tools</h3>
<p>Traditional AI plugins sit inside your WordPress dashboard. You open a post, click a button, and the plugin generates a paragraph, rewrites a sentence, or suggests a headline. The human drives every action.</p>
<p>Plugins like Yoast SEO and RankMath analyze content and flag issues. They do not fix those issues for you. You still make every edit manually.</p>
<h3>Agents: Proactive Operators</h3>
<p>AI agents operate outside the dashboard. They connect through APIs, assess your entire site, and execute multi-step workflows autonomously. You define the goal. The agent handles execution.</p>
